ENTRY            K2611   20260503   20260508   20260508       K024
SUBENT        K2611001   20260503   20260508   20260508       K024
BIB                 12         26
TITLE      Photonuclear reaction of Iodine-129 with laser-compton
           scattering gamma-rays using Nd:YVO4 laser and electron
           storage ring
AUTHOR     (K.Horikawa, T.Mochizuki, S.Miyamoto, S.Amano,
            T.Watanabe, D.Li, K.Imasaki, Y.Izawa)
INSTITUTE  (2JPNHIT)
           (2JPNJPN) Institute for Laser Technology, Osaka
REFERENCE  (J,RLE,39,445,2011)
DECAY-DATA (53-I-128,25.MIN,DG,443.,0.126)
INC-SOURCE Beam intensity is 5.0E+05 PPS.
           (LCS)
SAMPLE     - Chemical-form of target is element.
           - Physical-form of target is solid.
           - Target-thickness: 6 g/cm3
METHOD     (ACTIV)
FACILITY   (ESTRG,2JPNHIT) NewSUBARU at Ring for Accelerating and
                           Storage
DETECTOR   (GE)
ERR-ANALYS (ERR-SYS) major factor due to the alignment accuracy
                     between the gamma-ray beam and the target
                     axes
           (ERR-1) the number of iodine-129
           (ERR-2) flux of gamma-ray
           (ERR-3) gamma-ray energy spread
           (ERR-4) detector efficiency
HISTORY    (20171206C) Ichko
ENDBIB              26
COMMON               5          3
ERR-SYS    ERR-1      ERR-2      ERR-3      ERR-4
PER-CENT   PER-CENT   PER-CENT   PER-CENT   PER-CENT
 50.        1.         2.         3.         10.
ENDCOMMON            3
